{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block body %}
<div class="container">
    <div class="container">
        <header class="border-bottom pb-4 mb-5">
            <h1 class="mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="lead text-body-secondary mb-0"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> July 10, 2026</p>
        </header>

        <p class="border-bottom pb-4 mb-5 larger">At FileDrop Pro, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy
            explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you interact with our platform.
        </p>

        <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
        <p>We collect minimal data necessary to provide a seamless and secure file-sharing experience:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Your email address and authentication credentials.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage and Technical Data:</strong> Metadata about your file transactions,
                including IP addresses, browser types, device identifiers, and timestamps.</li>
            <li><strong>Uploaded Files:</strong> The files you (or your clients) upload directly to our platform.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
        <p>We use the collected information to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Provide, maintain, and secure the FileDrop service.</li>
            <li>Authenticate user accounts and manage storage allocations.</li>
            <li>Monitor system health, detect malicious activity, and prevent platform abuse.</li>
            <li>Communicate essential account notifications or technical updates.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="ms-3"><strong>Our Data Philosophy:</strong>
            We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data or your uploaded content to third-party advertisers or
            data brokers.
        </p>

        <h3>3. Data Storage, Retention, and Security</h3>
        <p><strong>Security Measures:</strong>
            We implement industry-standard administrative, technical, and physical safeguards (including transport
            layer encryption) designed to protect your data from unauthorized access or alteration.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Retention:</strong>
            Files dropped anonymously or configured with expiration dates are permanently purged from our storage
            infrastructure automatically once their expiration threshold is reached. Active account storage persists
            until explicitly deleted by the user or upon account closure.
        </p>

        <h3>4. Third-Party Services</h3>
        <p>We may utilize trusted third-party service providers to handle tasks like cloud infrastructure hosting,
            payment processing (if applicable), or error-logging. These providers have access to your data only to
            perform specified operational tasks on our behalf and are legally obligated not to disclose or use it for
            any other purpose.
        </p>

        <h3>5. Your Rights and Choices</h3>
        <p>Depending on your jurisdiction (such as under the GDPR or CCPA), you may have the right to access, correct,
            restrict, or request the complete deletion of your personal data and account metrics. You can manage most
            of these details directly from your FileDrop Account Settings dashboard or by reaching out to our support
            team.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
